27#ifndef _DT_INTTAB_H
28#define _DT_INTTAB_H
29
30#pragma ident "%Z%%M% %I% %E% SMI"
31
32#include <dtrace.h>
33
34#ifdef __cplusplus
35extern "C" {
36#endif
37
38typedef struct dt_inthash {
39 struct dt_inthash *inh_hash; /* next dt_inthash in hash chain */
40 struct dt_inthash *inh_next; /* next dt_inthash in output table */
41 uint64_t inh_value; /* value associated with this element */
42 uint_t inh_index; /* index associated with this element */
43 uint_t inh_flags; /* flags (see below) */
44} dt_inthash_t;
45
46typedef struct dt_inttab {
47 dtrace_hdl_t *int_hdl; /* pointer back to library handle */
48 dt_inthash_t **int_hash; /* array of hash buckets */
49 uint_t int_hashlen; /* size of hash bucket array */
50 uint_t int_nelems; /* number of elements hashed */
51 dt_inthash_t *int_head; /* head of table in index order */
52 dt_inthash_t *int_tail; /* tail of table in index order */
53 uint_t int_index; /* next index to hand out */
54} dt_inttab_t;
55
56#define DT_INT_PRIVATE 0 /* only a single ref for this entry */
57#define DT_INT_SHARED 1 /* multiple refs can share entry */
58
59extern dt_inttab_t *dt_inttab_create(dtrace_hdl_t *);
60extern void dt_inttab_destroy(dt_inttab_t *);
61extern int dt_inttab_insert(dt_inttab_t *, uint64_t, uint_t);
62extern uint_t dt_inttab_size(const dt_inttab_t *);
63extern void dt_inttab_write(const dt_inttab_t *, uint64_t *);
64
65#ifdef __cplusplus
66}
67#endif
68
69#endif /* _DT_INTTAB_H */
70
